│ THOUGHT: The bug is that IndVarSimplify narrows an icmp with the "samesign" qualifier, which is unsafe because changing bit-width can change whether operands share the same sign,       │
│ introducing poison. The right fix is to make the compare-narrowing logic bail out when the icmp has samesign. This narrowing typically happens in SimplifyIndVar utilities used by       │
│ IndVarSimplify. I will:                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ - Inspect SimplifyIndVar.cpp and IndVarSimplify.cpp around compare simplifications with limited output.                                                                                  │
│ - Insert a conservative guard: if an ICmpInst has the samesign qualifier, skip any cast-elimination/narrowing transformations for that compare.                                          │
│ - Build and run submit-patch to validate.                                                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
